How we've paid for music from 1983 to today, in one mesmerizing GIF
The internet has radically changed the way we consume and purchase music, but it isn't the first game-changer. In 30 years, the music industry has moved from   to cassettes to CDs to downloads to music subscriptions. In this GIF, created by  , you can watch those revenues change.   
